{"title_page": "Cabaj-\u010c\u00e1por", "text_new": "[[Image:Okres nitra.png|thumb|right|300px|Nitra district in the Nitra region]]\n'''Cabaj-\u010c\u00e1por''' is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Nitra District]] in western central [[Slovakia]], in the [[Nitra Region]].<ref>http://www.e-obce.sk/obec/cabajcapor/cabaj---capor.html</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe village was first mentioned in 1156 in [[history|historical records]]\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[village]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 165 metres and covers an [[area]] of 34.422&nbsp;km\u00b2. It has a [[population]] of about 3570 people.\n\n==Ethnicity==\nThe village is approximately 98% [[Slovaks|Slovak]].\n\n==Facilities==\nThe village has a public [[library]] and [[Association football pitch|football pitch]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of municipalities and towns in Slovakia]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==Genealogical resources==\nThe records for genealogical research are available at the state archive \"Statny Archiv in Nitra, Slovakia\"\n\n* Roman Catholic church records (births/marriages/deaths): 1763-1899 (parish A)\n* Lutheran church records (births/marriages/deaths): 1887-1954 (parish B)\n\n==External links==\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20071116010355/http://www.statistics.sk/mosmis/eng/run.html\n*[http://www.cisarik.com/0_CabajCapor_Nitra_NI_Nyitra_Nitra.html'''Surnames''' of living people in CabajCapor]\n\n{{Nitra District}}\n{{coord|48|15|N|18|02|E|region:SK_type:city|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cabaj-Capor}}\n[[Category:Villages and municipalities in Nitra District]]\n\n\n{{Nitra-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Okres nitra.png|thumb|right|300px|Nitra district in the Nitra region]]\n'''Cabaj-\u010c\u00e1por''' is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Nitra District]] in western central [[Slovakia]], in the [[Nitra Region]].<ref>http://www.e-obce.sk/obec/cabajcapor/cabaj---capor.html</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe village was first mentioned in 1156 in [[history|historical records]]\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[village]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 165 metres and covers an [[area]] of 34.422&nbsp;km\u00b2. It has a [[population]] of about 3570 people.\n\n==Ethnicity==\nThe village is approximately 98% [[Slovaks|Slovak]].\n\n==Facilities==\nThe village has a public [[library]] and [[Association football pitch|football pitch]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of municipalities and towns in Slovakia]]\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==Genealogical resources==\nThe records for genealogical research are available at the state archive \"Statny Archiv in Nitra, Slovakia\"\n\n* Roman Catholic church records (births/marriages/deaths): 1763-1899 (parish A)\n* Lutheran church records (births/marriages/deaths): 1887-1954 (parish B)\n\n==External links==\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20071116010355/http://www.statistics.sk/mosmis/eng/run.html\n*[http://www.cisarik.com/0_CabajCapor_Nitra_NI_Nyitra_Nitra.html'''Surnames''' of living people in CabajCapor]\n\n{{Nitra District}}\n{{coord|48|15|N|18|02|E|region:SK_type:city|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cabaj-Capor}}\n[[Category:Villages and municipalities in Nitra District]]\n\n\n{{Nitra-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cabaj-%C4%8C%C3%A1por"}
{"title_page": "B\u017eany, Stropkov District", "text_new": "[[Image:Okres stropkov.png|thumb|right|350px|Location of [[Stropkov District]] in the [[Pre\u0161ov Region]].]]\n'''B\u017eany''' is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in [[Stropkov District]] in the [[Pre\u0161ov Region]] of north-eastern [[Slovakia]].\n\n==History==\nIn [[history|historical records]] the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1410.\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[municipality]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 170 metres and covers an [[area]] of 17.064&nbsp;km\u00b2. It has a [[population]] of about 172 people.\n\n==Genealogical resources==\n\nThe records for genealogical research are available at the state archive \"Statny Archiv in Presov, Slovakia\"\n\n* Roman Catholic church records (births/marriages/deaths): 1802-1895 (parish B)\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of municipalities and towns in Slovakia]]\n\n==External links==\n*https://web.archive.org/web/20071116010355/http://www.statistics.sk/mosmis/eng/run.html\n*[http://www.cisarik.com/0_Bzany_Stropkov_PV_Zemplen_Zemplin.html'''Surnames''' of living people in Bzany]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Stropkov District}}\n\n{{coord|49|06|N|21|39|E|region:SK_type:city|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bzany, Stropkov District}}\n[[Category:Villages and municipalities in Stropkov District]]\n[[Category:Zempl\u00edn (region)]]\n\n\n{{Pre\u0161ov-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[Image:Okres stropkov.png|thumb|right|350px|Location of [[Stropkov District]] in the [[Pre\u0161ov Region]].]]\n'''B\u017eany''' is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in [[Stropkov District]] in the [[Pre\u0161ov Region]] of north-eastern [[Slovakia]].\n\n==History==\nIn [[history|historical records]] the [[village]] was first mentioned in 1410.\n\n==Geography==\nThe [[municipality]] lies at an [[altitude]] of 170 metres and covers an [[area]] of 17.064&nbsp;km\u00b2. It has a [[population]] of about 172 people.\n\n==