{"title_page": "Saudi Authority for Data and Artificial Intelligence", "text_new": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name = \n| seal = \n| logo = \n| formed = 30 August 2019\n| jurisdiction = [[Government of Saudi Arabia]]\n| headquarters = [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Riyadh]]\n| employees = \n| budget = \n| chief1_name = Abdullah Al-Ghamdi\n| chief1_position = \n| chief2_name = \n| chief2_position = \n| chief3_name = \n| chief3_position = \n| chief4_name = \n| chief4_position = \n| chief5_name = \n| chief5_position = \n| chief6_name = \n| chief6_position = \n| chief7_name = \n| chief7_position = \n| chief8_name = \n| chief8_position = \n| chief9_name = \n| chief9_position = \n| parent_department = \n| website = \n}}\n\nThe '''Saudi Data and Artificial Intelligence Authority''' is a government agency in [[Saudi Arabia]] that was established by a royal decree on 30 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1547546/saudi-arabia|title=King Salman issues royal decrees, including creation of industry and resources ministry|date=2019-08-30|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> The authority has three other bodies linked to it. Two of which were also created by a royal decree on the same day.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://saudigazette.com.sa/article/575953|title=King Salman issues royal decrees, including setting up of industry and resources ministry|date=2019-08-30|website=Saudigazette|language=English|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> These two bodies are a center called \"The National Centre for [[Artificial intelligence|Artificial Intelligence]]\" and an office called \"The National Data Management Office.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tahawultech.com/region/saudi-arabia/national-centre-for-ai-to-drive-saudi-arabias-digital-future-minister/|title=National Centre for AI to drive Saudi Arabia's digital future: minister|date=2019-09-01|website=TahawulTech.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The third is the National Information Center, which is an existing entity.\n\n== Structure ==\nThe authority is directly linked to the Prime Minister and will be governed by a board of directors chaired by the Deputy Prime Minister.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia}}\n\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Government agencies of Saudi Arabia]]\n\n\n{{SaudiArabia-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox government agency\n| name = \n| seal = \n| logo = \n| formed = 30 August 2019\n| jurisdiction = [[Government of Saudi Arabia]]\n| headquarters = [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Riyadh]]\n| employees = \n| budget = \n| chief1_name = Abdullah Al-Ghamdi\n| chief1_position = \n| chief2_name = \n| chief2_position = \n| chief3_name = \n| chief3_position = \n| chief4_name = \n| chief4_position = \n| chief5_name = \n| chief5_position = \n| chief6_name = \n| chief6_position = \n| chief7_name = \n| chief7_position = \n| chief8_name = \n| chief8_position = \n| chief9_name = \n| chief9_position = \n| parent_department = \n| website = \n}}\n\nThe '''Saudi Data and Artificial Intelligence Authority''' is a government agency in [[Saudi Arabia]] that was established by a royal decree on 30 August 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arabnews.com/node/1547546/saudi-arabia|title=King Salman issues royal decrees, including creation of industry and resources ministry|date=2019-08-30|website=Arab News|language=en|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> The authority has three other bodies linked to it. Two of which were also created by a royal decree on the same day.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://saudigazette.com.sa/article/575953|title=King Salman issues royal decrees, including setting up of industry and resources ministry|date=2019-08-30|website=Saudigazette|language=English|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref> These two bodies are a center called \"The National Centre for [[Artificial intelligence|Artificial Intelligence]]\" and an office called \"The National Data Management Office.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tahawultech.com/region/saudi-arabia/national-centre-for-ai-to-drive-saudi-arabias-digital-future-minister/|title=National Centre for AI to drive Saudi Arabia's digital future: minister|date=2019-09-01|website=TahawulTech.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-09-01}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> The third is the National Information Center, which is an existing entity.\n\n== Structure ==\nThe authority is directly linked to the Prime Minister and will be governed by a board of directors chaired by the Deputy Prime Minister.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n{{Portal|Saudi Arabia}}\n\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Saudi Arabia]]\n[[Category:Government agencies of Saudi Arabia]]\n\n\n{{SaudiArabia-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saudi_Authority_for_Data_and_Artificial_Intelligence"}
